= SDL_GetRenderTarget =
Use this function to get the current render target.




== Syntax ==
```c++
SDL_Texture* SDL_GetRenderTarget(SDL_Renderer* renderer)
```


== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''renderer'''
|the rendering context
|}


== Return Value ==
Returns the current render target or NULL for the default render target.


